@node "Install" "Installation Info"
The installation of the game is simple...follow the 8 steps below, and you'll
be set!

1) Make a directory in your DOORS: directory called Dice

2) Make a directory in your DOORS: directory called GameData

3) Copy 10000 to the DOORS:Dice Directory

4) Copy TopDice to the DOORS:Dice Directory

5) Edit your DLG.start (located in s:) file to include the following line:
   ASSIGN GameData: Doors:GameData

6) Edit your Login.DLGBatch (located in DLGConfig:Batch) file to include:
   DOORS:Dice/TopDice

7) Add a menu item and set it up to look like the following:
   [ 1] Letter:                   1
   [ 2] Executable: (path/name)   DOORS:DICE/10000 "%NAME" 5
   [ 4] Description:              10,000 dice game!
   [ 5] Type:                     Executable
   [ 6] Help File:                DOORS/1
   [ 7] Lower level:              5
   [ 8] Upper level:              255
   [ 9] Hidden:                   NO
   [10] Load type:                OVERLAY
   [11] Ask user if sure:         NO
   [12] Pend messages:            YES
   [13] Cli mode:                 NO
   [14] Pause on completion:      NO
   [15] Log value:                200
   [16] Activity string:          Playing 10,000
   [17] Priority:                 DEFAULT
   [18] Edit help file

8) You're done!

========== Here's a description of the command line for 10000:

The first entry is "%NAME" which give 10,000 the user's name and allows the
program to get other information from DLG.

The second entry is 5 which is the number of turns per day.  This is the
recommended setting, and should make a game last about 4-6 days.  You can
change it if you want, but I don't recommend it! :)
==========
The GameData directory and assign are done for various reasons, but they won't
be apparent until a later date.  Namely when you run another game of mine...
just wait, all the data will go to ONE directory.
==========
This game makes use of the TelePro Technologies include files, and those are
used without specific permission from TPT.
==========
I'll skip the usual legal crap, but let it suffice to say, I own and hold the
copyright on this game! :)  It is @{"Shareware" alink "Register" 0}, and that is all.

I hope you enjoy the game, and have fun playing!  
@endnode

